{"word":"ἐξανίημι","slug":"ἐξανίημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξανίημι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ανήσω</el>) (or <el>-ήσομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to send forth, let loose</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to send forth from</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to let go</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to slacken, undo</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—and <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to slacken, relax</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ὀργῆς ἐξανείς</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}